The paper deals with hybrid analog/digital precoding for millimeter wave MIMO systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of RF beamforming vectors taken from a quantized codebook, which is a topic related to signal processing (cs.SY) and millimeter wave technology (cs.MM). Finally, the paper proposes a low-complexity algorithm for the design of the hybrid precoders, which is a topic related to networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
